> My buddy here at work is obsessed with all things from Asia, 
particularly Japan.  He just told me that you cannot change the oil on 
the HiAce.  Tells me that they are designed to make an oil change 
difficult because of their environmental regulations.  Also claims that 
it is cheaper to buy a new HiAce than it is to replace the motor.  An 
interesting tale,.. anybody know if it's valid?  Are HiAce's really built 
that way?  Unfortunate...
